      "question": "In $\\triangle ABC$, a circle is inscribed such that it touches the sides $AB$, $BC$, and $AC$ at points $P$, $Q$, and $R$ respectively. If $AB = 12 \\text{ cm}$, $BC = 8 \\text{ cm}$, and $AC = 10 \\text{ cm}$, determine the lengths of the segments $AP$, $BQ$, and $CR$.",
      "answer": "$AP = 7 \\text{ cm}$, $BQ = 5 \\text{ cm}$, $CR = 3 \\text{ cm}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let $AP = AR = x$, $BP = BQ = y$, and $CQ = CR = z$ based on the property that tangent lengths from an external point to a circle are equal.",
          "Set up a system of linear equations: $x + y = 12$, $y + z = 8$, and $x + z = 10$. Solve for $x$, $y$, and $z$ by adding the equations and subtracting individual ones."
        ],
        "derivation": "$AP=AR=x, \\; BP=BQ=y, \\; CQ=CR=z \\\\ x+y=12, \\; y+z=8, \\; x+z=10 \\\\ (x+y)+(y+z)+(x+z) = 12+8+10 \\Rightarrow 2(x+y+z) = 30 \\Rightarrow x+y+z = 15 \\\\ x = (x+y+z) - (y+z) = 15 - 8 = 7 \\text{ cm} \\\\ y = (x+y+z) - (x+z) = 15 - 10 = 5 \\text{ cm} \\\\ z = (x+y+z) - (x+y) = 15 - 12 = 3 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
